   There is no perfect way to do stuff like that.  If you go out on a limb and start encouraging and helping people, youre going to make mistakes and have miscommunication.  Its just a consequence of making the effort.  It looks fine to me, but then, Ive accused people of being really laughably obvious sockpuppets... and then had a few conversations with them later, where it was clear that they just happened to show up at the perfectly wrong time.  You will make mistakes, and you will come across wrong... unless you stay absolutely silent.  If everybody did that, we wouldnt have the wiki.  So dont worry about making mistakes, just do the best that you can and know that when you do get slammed because youre misinterpreted, or if you read a situation wrong, there are plenty of people who appreciated all the times you got it right and helped them out.   Youll also get better the more times you do it.  In short, it looks fine, and that kind of outreach is both a tricky thing to do and a really important aspect of how the wiki community helps and encourages each other.   Im sure Im not alone in appreciating your effort. Users/JabberWokky Evan JabberWokky Edwards
